Program: The Forum
Title: 08/08/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p008xmy3
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 8 Aug 2010
Eminent sociologist Amitai Etzioni, says if our modern consumer society is the problem, then the answer is a ‘communitarian’ approach. But can this really work? Getting beyond the individual is also what Nigerian novelist Teju Cole explores. In his case it’s not people around him, it’s communing with the past inhabitants of cities. And from individual to common ownership in music: should songs belong to everyone? German musicologist Dr Daniel Müllensiefen dissects musical plagiarism. Illustration by Graeme Davis. Show less